From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: roslyn <noreply@platform.uno>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: fall back to interpreter when gsharedvt_out_sig wrapper
 is missing in aot-only mode

In LLVMOnly+Interp mode (the WASM worker scenario), the interpreter can
encounter a call to an AOT-compiled method whose gsharedvt_out_sig
wrapper for the call signature is not present in the AOT image. The
AOT compiler only emits gsharedvt_out wrappers for signatures it
observes during method compilation (cfg->method's sig, cfg->signatures);
some interp-only call sites use a signature the compiler never saw,
so the wrapper is missing.

When this happened, `init_jit_call_info`
(mono/mini/interp/interp.c) hit:

  jit_wrapper = mono_jit_compile_method_jit_only (wrapper, error);
  mono_error_assert_ok (error);

The mono_jit_compile_method_jit_only call returns the error
"Attempting to JIT compile method ... while running in aot-only mode"
and the assert aborts the runtime.

A widening fix on the AOT-compiler side (patch 0007) helps but is
necessarily incomplete: it covers signatures observed in
cfg->signatures, not signatures that only interp callers know about.
A robust solution requires a runtime-side fallback.

This patch adds that fallback. When `mono_jit_compile_method_jit_only`
fails on the wrapper, we ask the interpreter for an entry trampoline
for the target method via
`mini_get_interp_callbacks ()->create_method_pointer_llvmonly`. That
returns a MonoFtnDesc whose .addr is a gsharedvt_in_sig (or interp_in)
wrapper for the method's underlying signature, and whose .arg is an
InterpMethod entry descriptor. The arg-passing shape matches what
jit_call_cb already uses for the no_wrapper path (args... , extra_arg),
so we splice the interp trampoline in via that same code path by
setting:

  cinfo->no_wrapper = TRUE;
  cinfo->addr       = interp_ftndesc->addr;
  cinfo->extra_arg  = interp_ftndesc->arg;

`do_jit_call` consequently invokes the interpreter entry trampoline
with the same args layout it would have passed to the missing
gsharedvt_out_sig wrapper. The interpreter runs the method's IL
directly; AOT-compiled code is bypassed for THIS specific call.

Trade-offs:
- Slower than calling the AOT-compiled code through a real
  gsharedvt_out wrapper, but correct and avoids a g_assert-driven
  runtime exit.
- Depends on a matching gsharedvt_in_sig wrapper being present in the
  AOT image. The AOT compiler emits IN wrappers from a wider source
  set (cfg->signatures of every compiled method) than OUT wrappers,
  so in practice the IN wrapper usually exists when the OUT one is
  missing. If the IN wrapper is also missing,
  create_method_pointer_llvmonly will assert internally — at that
  point the original abort behaviour is the floor.

Concrete repro from roslyn (Roslyn-hosting worker, .NET 10,
LLVMOnly+Interp):

  [MONO] * Assertion at mono/mini/interp/interp.c, function:
  init_jit_call_info, Attempting to JIT compile method '(wrapper
  other) void object:gsharedvt_out_sig (intptr,
  Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CompoundUseSiteInfo`1<object>&, object&,
  object&, intptr)' while running in aot-only mode.

With this patch applied, the same call dispatches through the
interpreter and proceeds without aborting the worker.

---
 src/mono/mono/mini/interp/interp.c | 59 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 52 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/mono/mono/mini/interp/interp.c b/src/mono/mono/mini/interp/interp.c
index 0a12875dcce..f2af8a2a0e7 100644
--- a/src/mono/mono/mini/interp/interp.c
+++ b/src/mono/mono/mini/interp/interp.c
@@ -2731,21 +2731,66 @@ init_jit_call_info (InterpMethod *rmethod, MonoError *error)
 	}

 	gpointer jit_wrapper = NULL;
+	gboolean interp_fallback = FALSE;
 	if (need_wrapper) {
 		MonoMethod *wrapper = mini_get_gsharedvt_out_sig_wrapper (sig);
 		jit_wrapper = mono_jit_compile_method_jit_only (wrapper, error);
-		mono_error_assert_ok (error);
+		if (!is_ok (error)) {
+			/*
+			 * The gsharedvt_out_sig wrapper for this signature is not in the
+			 * AOT image and we cannot JIT it in aot-only mode (typically
+			 * LLVMOnly+Interp on WASM). Rather than aborting the runtime,
+			 * route the call through the interpreter: ask the interp callbacks
+			 * for an entry trampoline that, when invoked with the same arg
+			 * layout we would have used for the missing wrapper, runs METHOD's
+			 * IL through the interpreter.
+			 *
+			 * Why this works: create_method_pointer_llvmonly produces a
+			 * MonoFtnDesc whose addr is a gsharedvt_in_sig (or interp_in)
+			 * wrapper for the method's underlying signature, and whose arg is
+			 * an InterpMethod entry descriptor. The arg-passing shape matches
+			 * what jit_call_cb already emits for the no_wrapper path
+			 * (args... , extra_arg), so we splice it into cinfo via the same
+			 * no_wrapper code path.
+			 *
+			 * Caveats:
+			 *   - This is slower than calling the AOT-compiled code through
+			 *     a real gsharedvt_out wrapper, but it is correct and avoids
+			 *     a g_assert-driven runtime exit.
+			 *   - It depends on a matching gsharedvt_in_sig wrapper being
+			 *     present in the AOT image. The AOT compiler emits IN
+			 *     wrappers from a wider source set (cfg->signatures of every
+			 *     compiled method) than OUT wrappers, so in practice the IN
+			 *     wrapper usually exists when the OUT one is missing.
+			 *     create_method_pointer_llvmonly will assert if the IN
+			 *     wrapper is also missing -- at that point the original
+			 *     behaviour (abort) is the floor.
+			 */
+			mono_error_cleanup (error);
+			error_init (error);
+
+			MonoFtnDesc *interp_ftndesc = mini_get_interp_callbacks ()->create_method_pointer_llvmonly (method, FALSE, error);
+			mono_error_assert_ok (error);
+			g_assert (interp_ftndesc);
+
+			cinfo->no_wrapper = TRUE;
+			cinfo->addr = interp_ftndesc->addr;
+			cinfo->extra_arg = interp_ftndesc->arg;
+			interp_fallback = TRUE;
+		}
 	}

-	if (mono_llvm_only) {
-		gboolean caller_gsharedvt = !need_wrapper;
-		cinfo->addr = mini_llvmonly_add_method_wrappers (method, addr, caller_gsharedvt, FALSE, &cinfo->extra_arg);
-	} else {
-		cinfo->addr = addr;
+	if (!interp_fallback) {
+		if (mono_llvm_only) {
+			gboolean caller_gsharedvt = !need_wrapper;
+			cinfo->addr = mini_llvmonly_add_method_wrappers (method, addr, caller_gsharedvt, FALSE, &cinfo->extra_arg);
+		} else {
+			cinfo->addr = addr;
+		}
+		cinfo->wrapper = jit_wrapper;
 	}

 	cinfo->sig = sig;
-	cinfo->wrapper = jit_wrapper;

 	if (sig->ret->type != MONO_TYPE_VOID) {
 		int mt = mono_mint_type (sig->ret);
--
2.43.0
